---
// Draft privacy notice for the marketing site. Original wording, with structure/ideas
// adapted from common SaaS-healthcare privacy notices. REVIEW WITH LEGAL COUNSEL before
// public launch. Reflects a consent-first cookie model and current "no tracking" state.
// TODO before launch: (1) add a postal address for privacy requests (recommended for
// CCPA/GDPR); (2) confirm product names + domains; (3) keep the "we do not sell/share"
// statement accurate if practices change.
import Layout from '../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Notice — Ophthalytics"
  description="How Ophthalytics collects, uses, shares, and protects personal information on our marketing website."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-brand-surface-blue">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-16 md:py-20">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-brand-muted">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-primary">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-ink">Privacy Notice</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-ink leading-tight">
        Privacy Notice
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-sm text-brand-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-16 md:py-20 space-y-10 text-brand-body leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Ophthalytics, Inc. ("Ophthalytics," "we," "us," or "our") is committed to respecting your
        privacy. This Privacy Notice ("Notice") explains how we collect, use, share, and otherwise
        process personal information about visitors to our marketing website, including
        ophthalytics.com and ophlx.com (the "Site").
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">What This Notice Does Not Cover</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">This Notice applies to the Site only. It does <strong>not</strong> apply to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>our clinical and diagnostic platforms and products (such as Ocula360, Nsight360, 2nd Opinion, and Ophthal360), which we provide to healthcare organizations under separate agreements and privacy terms;</li>
          <li>patient or health information we process on behalf of healthcare providers, clinics, or health systems. If you are a patient of an organization that uses our technology, please refer to that organization's privacy notice and direct any privacy requests to them;</li>
          <li>de-identified or anonymized information that cannot reasonably be linked to you; or</li>
          <li>personal information collected in connection with employment or job applications.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Personal Information We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The personal information we collect depends on how you interact with the Site and the
          choices you make.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Information you provide directly</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          When you submit a contact form, request a demo, subscribe to our newsletter, or otherwise
          communicate with us, we collect the information you choose to provide—which may include
          your name, email address, phone number, organization or employer, role, and the contents
          of your message.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Information collected automatically</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          When you visit the Site, certain technical information may be logged automatically by our
          hosting and security infrastructure—such as your IP address, browser type, device and
          operating-system information, the pages you view, the date and time of your visit, and the
          site you came from. We use this to operate, secure, and troubleshoot the Site.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We may also collect usage information through cookies and similar technologies, but only
          with your consent, as described in "Cookies and Similar Technologies" below.
          <strong>We do not currently use analytics, advertising, or other tracking cookies, and we
          do not track your browsing activity.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Information we infer</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We may infer limited information from the data above—for example, your general geographic
          location (such as city, region, or country) from your IP address.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4">
          You can choose not to provide personal information, and you can use browser or device
          controls to limit certain automatic collection. If you decline information that is
          necessary for a feature (such as a contact form), that feature may not be available or
          fully functional.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">What they are</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Cookies are small text files placed on your device by your browser; similar technologies
          include pixels, tags, and local storage. They can allow a website to recognize your
          browser over time.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Our approach—consent first</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We currently do not use analytics, advertising, or other non-essential cookies, and we do
          not track your activity. If we introduce non-essential cookies in the future (for example,
          website analytics), we will ask for your consent first through a cookie banner or similar
          control. You may decline. <strong>If you do not affirmatively consent, we will not set
          those cookies or track your activity through them.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If the Site uses any cookies that are strictly necessary for it to function or to keep it
          secure, those may be set without consent as permitted by law. They are not used to track
          you for advertising.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold text-brand-ink">Your controls</h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Cookie banner:</strong> where offered, you can accept or decline non-essential cookies and change your choice at any time.</li>
          <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> most browsers let you block or delete cookies. Disabling cookies may affect some features.</li>
          <li><strong>Do Not Track:</strong> because there is no common standard for "Do Not Track" (DNT) browser signals, the Site does not currently respond to them—however, because we do not track you without consent, your activity is not tracked regardless.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">How We Use Personal Information</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Respond to your inquiries and demo requests;</li>
          <li>Send communications you have requested, such as our newsletter and product updates;</li>
          <li>Operate, secure, maintain, and improve the Site;</li>
          <li>Understand how the Site is used (where analytics are enabled, with your consent);</li>
          <li>Send marketing communications about our products and events, from which you can opt out at any time; and</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">How We Share Personal Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>We do not sell your personal information, and we do not share it for
          cross-context behavioral advertising.</strong> We share personal information only as
          described here:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> vendors that perform services for us, such as website hosting, customer relationship management (CRM), email delivery, and—if enabled, with your consent—analytics. They may process personal information only on our behalf and under contract.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal and safety:</strong> when we believe it is necessary to comply with applicable law or valid legal process, enforce our terms, or protect the rights, property, or safety of Ophthalytics, our users, or others.</li>
          <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> in connection with a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of assets, consistent with this Notice.</li>
          <li><strong>With your consent</strong> or at your direction.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">We may also share de-identified information that cannot reasonably identify you.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Your Choices and Controls</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Access, correction, deletion:</strong> you can request to access, correct, or delete personal information we hold about you by contacting us (see "Contact Us"). We may need to verify your identity and may decline requests where permitted by law.</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing communications:</strong> you can opt out of marketing emails at any time using the unsubscribe link or by contacting us. We may still send non-promotional messages, such as responses to your inquiries.</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> see "Cookies and Similar Technologies" for your cookie choices.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Your U.S. State Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Depending on where you live, U.S. state privacy laws—such as the California Consumer
          Privacy Act, as amended (CCPA/CPRA)—may give you rights to know or access the personal
          information we collect about you, to request its correction or deletion, and to opt out of
          the "sale" or "sharing" of personal information and certain targeted advertising. As noted
          above, we do not sell or share personal information as those terms are defined under these
          laws, and we will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights. To exercise a
          right, contact us as described below; we will verify your request as required by law. You
          may also use an authorized agent where permitted.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">European, UK &amp; Swiss Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you are in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you may have
          rights under the GDPR (and UK GDPR) to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object to our
          processing of your personal information, and to data portability. Where we rely on consent,
          you may withdraw it at any time. We process personal information on lawful bases including
          your consent, our legitimate interests in operating and improving the Site, and compliance
          with legal obligations. You may lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority,
          though we encourage you to contact us first.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We retain personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described
          in this Notice, comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our
          agreements, after which we delete or de-identify it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We are based in the United States, and the personal information we collect is stored and
          processed in the United States and other countries where we or our service providers
          operate. These countries may have data-protection laws different from your own. Where
          required, we use appropriate safeguards for international transfers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Security</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We take reasonable and appropriate administrative, technical, and physical measures to
          protect personal information against unauthorized access, use, disclosure, alteration, and
          destruction. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot
          guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The Site is intended for a general, professional audience and is not directed to children.
          We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has
          provided us personal information, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps to
          delete it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Changes to This Notice</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may update this Notice from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated"
          date above and, if the changes are material, provide additional notice or obtain consent as
          required by law.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you have questions or requests regarding this Notice or your personal information,
          contact us at
          <a href="mailto:info@ophthalytics.com" class="text-brand-primary font-semibold hover:underline">info@ophthalytics.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
